<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>VT 365 Diesel Engine - 2004 Model Year - CYLINDER HEAD AND VALVE TRAIN - Installation - Glow Plug Sleeve
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s26504.4.2" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Glow Plug Sleeve</title>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To prevent personal injury or death, wear safety glasses with side shields to protect eyes. Limit
                    compressed air pressure to 207 kPa (30 psi).
                </para>
            </warning>
            <note>
                <para>Make sure the glow plug recess was cleaned out with the glow plug sleeve brush, rinsed with a
                    suitable cleaning solution, and blown out with shop air.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f2650474" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd08/d0862.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Application of liquid gasket to sleeve</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Wall (end)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Upper wall (top)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply Liquid Gasket (RTV) to the wall and upper wall on the glow plug sleeve.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650475" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figD08/D08192.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Installation of glow plug sleeve</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Glow Plug Sleeve Installer</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Glow plug sleeve</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install glow plug sleeve in cylinder head with the Glow Plug Sleeve Installer . Continue to
                tap the Glow Plug Sleeve Installer until the sleeve bottoms out in the recess.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean glow plug sleeve with a Glow Plug Sleeve Brush (nylon) and solvent. Make sure liquid
                gasket is cleaned out before it hardens.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
